This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it presents an optimization-based motion planning algorithm for a manipulator. The paper also takes into account fluid dynamics constraints, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with transferring liquid from a source to a target container, which could involve visual perception. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possibility as the optimization approach can incorporate various constraints. Finally, Mechanical Engineering (cs.ME) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the dynamics of fluid manipulation.
